title: Fetching Road Data with `fetch_roads()`
text: example specify rectangular area using bounding box. default, fetch_roads() returns roads intersect box. Setting crop = TRUE trim box’s boundaries.   shown plots, crop = TRUE trims road geometries precisely red-dashed boundary.
code: # Define a bounding box (e.g., around Sakae area, Japan) sakae_bbox <- create_bbox(north =  35.17377,                           south =  35.16377,                           east  = 136.91590,                           west  = 136.90090)  # 1. Fetch roads without cropping (default) roads_default <- fetch_roads(sakae_bbox) plot(roads_default$geometry, lwd = 2) plot(convert_bbox_to_polygon(sakae_bbox), add = TRUE, border = "red", lty = 2, lwd = 2) # 2. Fetch roads with cropping roads_cropped <- fetch_roads(sakae_bbox, crop = TRUE) plot(roads_cropped$geometry, lwd = 2) plot(convert_bbox_to_polygon(sakae_bbox), add = TRUE, border = "red", lty = 2, lwd = 2)

what: Fetching by center point and radius
title: Fetching Road Data with `fetch_roads()`
text: can specify center point (longitude latitude) search radius meters. get roads trimmed circular area, must set crop = TRUE cricle_crop = TRUE  plot shows road network perfectly contained within specified circular boundary.

title: Convolute a spatiotemporal network to perform TNKDE — convolute_spatiotemporal_network
text: function performs Temporal Network Kernel Density Estimation (TNKDE) spatiotemporal network object. calculates density values across network's segments series time points.

title: Convolute a spatiotemporal network to perform TNKDE — convolute_spatiotemporal_network
code: convolute_spatiotemporal_network(   segmented_network,   kernel_space = compute_epanechnikov,   kernel_time = compute_epanechnikov,   bandwidth_space = 3,   bandwidth_time = 2,   time_points = 0:23,   use_esd = TRUE,   correct_boundary_effects = TRUE )

title: Convolute a spatiotemporal network to perform TNKDE — convolute_spatiotemporal_network
text: segmented_network spatiotemporal network object, typically output create_spatiotemporal_network() followed set_events(). kernel_space spatial kernel function (default: compute_epanechnikov). kernel_time temporal kernel function (default: compute_epanechnikov). bandwidth_space spatial bandwidth (network's distance units). bandwidth_time temporal bandwidth (hours). time_points numeric vector time points (e.g., hours 0:23) estimate density. use_esd TRUE (default), uses Equal Split Discontinuous (ESD) kernel spatial smoothing account network intersections. correct_boundary_effects TRUE (default), corrects boundary effects normalizing kernel weights source sum 1.

title: Convolute a spatiotemporal network to perform TNKDE — convolute_spatiotemporal_network
text: input network object $segments component updated sf data frame spatial segments, now containing new columns (density_t_0, density_t_1, etc.) calculated density values. total density segments time points normalized sum 1.
